# Prescription & Lab Card Styling — All Accounts

**Apply to prescription and lab test workflow cards** — and any similar dashboard list cards (patient, professional, new, old, future).

## 1. Card Header Tint (Desktop + Mobile)

**Always** use a tinted header on both desktop and mobile:

```tsx
<CardHeader className="p-3 pt-2 pb-2 sm:p-4 sm:pb-3 border-b bg-sky-50/70 dark:bg-sky-950/25 space-y-1 sm:space-y-1.5">
```

- **Color:** `bg-sky-50/70` (light), `bg-sky-950/25` (dark)
- **Scope:** Both desktop and mobile — no responsive variant for the tint

## 2. Compact Layout (Mobile Only)

Use responsive classes so compact spacing applies **only on mobile** (< sm):

| Element | Mobile | Desktop (sm+) |
|--------|--------|---------------|
| Card | `gap-2 pb-2` | `gap-3 pb-3` |
| CardHeader | `p-3 pt-2 pb-2` | `p-4 pb-3` |
| CardContent | `p-3 pt-2 space-y-3` | `p-4 pt-3 space-y-4` |
| CardTitle | `text-base` | `text-lg` |
| Medication/result items | `py-2 px-3` | `py-3 px-4` |
| Grid gap | `gap-4` | `gap-6` |

## 3. Files to Keep in Sync

- `components/prescription-workflow.tsx` — prescription cards
- `components/lab-test-workflow.tsx` — lab test cards
- `app/(patient)/dashboard/prescriptions/page.tsx` — grid gap
- Any new workflow cards (e.g. referral, appointment cards)

## 4. Scope

**All new and future accounts** — changes are in shared components, so they apply to every user automatically. No per-account configuration.

## Do NOT

- Remove the header tint on mobile
- Apply compact spacing to desktop (keep desktop spacious)
- Use different tints per account type — same sky tint for all
